Mount Isa Mines Holding Ltd plans toacquire a 30 pct stake in Europe's largest primary copperproducer, Norddeutsche Affinerie AG, a spokesman forMetallgesellschaft AG said.    MIM intends to take Preussag AG's total 20 pct share in thecopper producer in exchange for some three pct of MIM's sharecapital. MIM will also take another 10 pct now held by DegussaAG, reducing Degussa's share to 30 pct from 40.Metallgesellschaft's share will remain at 40 pct.    The move is subject to approval of the federal carteloffice and supervisory boards of the companies involved. Reuter&#3;